        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1080754345" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12897078019097922440">FI-NAL-LY!! I&apos;ve read it all!!<br/>This is one of the few books I wanted to put away as soon as I started reading. Optimistic as I was, I read on and hoped it would become better. It didn&apos;t. It only got worse and worse, but I&apos;m too OCD to stop reading any book I started reading.<br/><br/>Bettelheim&apos;s approach is hardly scientific and leaves too less space for alternate conclusions. On top of that, he sounds like someone who knows the child&apos;s mind like nobody else and has taken some time to teach all this wonde</span>
  <span id="freeText12897078019097922440" style="display:none">FI-NAL-LY!! I've read it all!!<br />This is one of the few books I wanted to put away as soon as I started reading. Optimistic as I was, I read on and hoped it would become better. It didn't. It only got worse and worse, but I'm too OCD to stop reading any book I started reading.<br /><br />Bettelheim's approach is hardly scientific and leaves too less space for alternate conclusions. On top of that, he sounds like someone who knows the child's mind like nobody else and has taken some time to teach all this wonderful knowledge *do you sense my sarcasm?* (I will not start ranting on his sexism, but he calls the child 'he' and 'him', unless it is helpless and in need, then suddenly it is 'she' and 'her')<br /><br />Anyway, the connection between mice/rats and phallic association still eludes me and I'm sad to say Bettelheim totally ruined my innocent enjoyment of reading popular fairy tales like 'Beauty and the Beast', 'Snow White', 'Cinderella' and especially 'Jack and the Beanstalk'. I will now forever try to ban the phallic association, brought to me by Bettelheim, with the beanstalk. <br /><br />Please, if you plan to enjoy fairy tales for the rest of your life, do yourself a favour and don't even think of picking up this book to read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="12897078019097922440" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
